DC Exercise 8

Hongji Jiang

1

geom_point() Make scatter plot

geom_histogram() make histogram

ggplot() Build the initial plot object

scale_y_log10() Log axis for y

ylab() Creat label for y axis

facet_wrap() Make subplot(facet)

geom_segment() Draw a straight line between points (x, y) and (xend, yend)

xlim() range of x axis

facet_grid() Form a matrix of panels defined by row and column faceting variables

2

library(mosaicData)
library(ggplot2)
library(DataComputing)
a <- mosaicData::CPS85

A

a %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = wage)) + geom_density(aes(color = sex, fill = sex), alpha = 0.3) + facet_wrap( ~ married)

B

a %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = age, y = wage)) + facet_wrap(~married, ncol = 1) + geom_smooth( method = loess) + aes(color = sex)

C

a %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = age, y = wage)) + geom_smooth( method = loess) + facet_wrap(~sector, ncol = 3) + aes(color = sex) + xlim(10, 70) + ylim(0,25)

3

A

a %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = age, y = wage)) +
  geom_point()

B

a %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = age, y = wage, shape = sex)) +
  geom_point()

C

a %>%
  ggplot(aes(x = age, y = wage, shape = sex)) +
  geom_point() + facet_wrap(~married, ncol = 1)

D

a%>%
  ggplot(aes(x = age, y = wage, shape = married)) +
  geom_point() + ylim(0,30)
